official_title: A bill to provide temporary authority for the Secretary of Agriculture to sell timber from the U.S. Forest Service lands created from the public domain, and lands otherwise acquired by the United States, in Alaska consistent with various acts.

summary.text: Authorizes the Secretary of Agriculture to enter into contracts through September, 1977, for the sale of timber from national forests and other Federal forest lands in Alaska.

titles.title: A bill to provide temporary authority for the Secretary of Agriculture to sell timber from the U.S. Forest Service lands created from the public domain, and lands otherwise acquired by the United States, in Alaska consistent with various acts.
